The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Hari makes it 5 out of 5

Taiyuan: World junior champion P. Harikrishna continued with his demolition act and downed GM Wang Hao in 20 moves to stretch his lead by 1.5 points after five rounds of the Sanjin Hotel Cup Grandmasters tournament. 

Harikrishna, with five points, is followed by Armenian Tigran Petrosian and Chinese Bu Xiangzhi (3.5 each). 

Another half-point behind are Alexander Motylev (Russia) and Wang Yue (China) with the former having played a game less. A pack of four, including the worlds youngest ever GM Sergey Karjakin of Ukraine, is sixth (2 each). 

Harikrishna has already gained 19 elo rating points from this event. 

Former world junior girls champion Zhoa Xuelost her fifth game on the trot, bowing to compatriot Bu Xiangzhi. The days two other games ? English GM Luke McShane against Motylev and Wang Yue versus hold Karjakin ? were drawn. (PTI) 




